N:standup-meeting
D:Facilitate useful daily standups, daily scrums, async check-ins, or walk-the-board delivery syncs without turning them into manager-facing status theater. Use for daily coordination, blocker triage, and remote-team check-ins rather than planning or retrospectives.
G:standup-meeting daily-scrum async-standup blocker-triage agile

U[5]:
  run a short daily sync for active sprint or delivery work
  convert a vague standup into a board-first or blocker-first flow
  create an async check-in format for distributed teams
  surface blocked work, review-ready items, and follow-up owners
  reset a noisy standup ritual that has become too long or low-signal

X[3]:
  backlog decomposition or sprint-candidate shaping -> task-planning
  story points, sizing, or forecast ranges -> task-estimation
  completed-work reflection or process change -> sprint-retrospective

S[5]{n,action}:
  1,Identify the standup mode
  2,Choose the lightest useful standup format
  3,Center the sync on work in motion and blockers
  4,Capture blocker owners and follow-ups
  5,Return a concise standup packet

R[5]:
  keep the sync tied to active work rather than personal theater
  make blockers and owners visible
  avoid turning the standup into planning or estimation
  keep problem-solving outside the main ritual unless blocker triage is explicit
  end with a recommended next move
